# Load MNIST data
(train_images, train_labels), (test_images, test_labels)= tf.keras.datasets.mnist.load_data()
# Encode
train_labels_encoded = to_categorical(train_labels)
test_labels_encoded = to_categorical(test_labels)
# Reshape
train_images_reshaped = np.reshape(train_images, (60000, 784))
test_images_reshaped = np.reshape(test_images, (10000, 784))
train_images_norm = train_images_reshaped.astype('float32') / 255
test_images_norm = test_images_reshaped.astype('float32') / 255
final_val_images, final_train_images = train_images_norm[:5000], train_images_norm[5000:]
final_val_labels, final_train_labels = train_labels_encoded[:5000], train_labels_encoded[5000:]
In[]:
# Figure out best activation to use
model_dict_activation = {}
working_activations = []
failed_activations = []
activation_functions = ['deserialize', 'elu', 'exponential', 'gelu', 'get', 'hard_sigmoid', 'hard_silu', 'hard_swish', 'leaky_relu', 'linear', 'log_softmax', 'mish', 'relu', 'relu_6', 'selu', 'serialize', 'sigmoid', 'silu', 'softmax', 'softplus', 'softsign', 'swish', 'tanh']
for activation in activation_functions:
  try:
    print(f"Training model with {activation}")
    # Build the DNN Model
    k.clear_session()
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(layers.Dense(10, activation=activation, input_shape=(28 * 28,)))
    model.add(layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax'))
    model.compile(optimizer='rmsprop', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    history = model.fit(final_train_images, final_train_labels, epochs=10, validation_data=(final_val_images, final_val_labels),callbacks=[tf.keras.callbacks.ModelCheckpoint(f"DNN_model_{activation}.keras",save_best_only=True,save_weights_only=False)])
    model_dict_activation[f'{activation}_model'] = history
    working_activations.append(activation)
  except ValueError:
    print(f"Error with {activation}")
    failed_activations.append(activation)

# Since Train remaining activations with several different nodes and 10 total epochs to keep it a shorter run
num_nodes_to_try = [1,2,4,8,16,32,64,128,256,512,1024]
model_node_activation_dict = {}
start = time.perf_counter()
for node in num_nodes_to_try:
  for activation in final_activations_to_try:
    print(f"Training model with {activation} and {node} nodes")
    # Build the DNN Model
    k.clear_session()
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(layers.Dense(node, activation=activation, input_shape=(28 * 28,)))
    model.add(layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax'))
    model.compile(optimizer='rmsprop', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    history = model.fit(final_train_images, final_train_labels, epochs=10, validation_data=(final_val_images, final_val_labels),callbacks=[tf.keras.callbacks.ModelCheckpoint(f"DNN_model_{node}Nodes.keras",save_best_only=True,save_weights_only=False)])
    model_node_activation_dict[f'{activation}_{node}_history'] = history
    model_node_activation_dict[f'{activation}_{node}_model'] = model
end = time.perf_counter()
print(f"Time taken: {end - start}")

  i=0
  for activation in activations_tried:
    history = model_node_activation_dict[f'{activation}_{node}_history']
    history_dictionary = history.history
    acc, loss, val_acc, val_loss = history_dictionary.keys()
    acc = history.history[acc]
    epochs = range(1, len(acc) + 1)
    plt.plot(epochs, acc, color_list[i], label=f'{activation}')
    i+=1
  plt.title(f'Training Accuracy {node} Nodes')
  plt.xlabel('Epochs')
  plt.ylabel('Accuracy')
  plt.legend()
  plt.show()
